commentary: Dawlat Zadran to Tamim Iqbal, FOUR runs nearly! Tamim has had trouble keeping the ball on the ground early in his innings. Another drive uppishly toward mid-off but Asghar Afghan is lead-footed and more or less falls over trying to flail his arms at it. Never came close to getting a hand to it whereas a more agile fielder might have created a chance.

commentary: Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Liton Das, OUT full on off, drives in the air to short cover and Afghanistan are claiming a catch! Watching live I thought it definitely short hopped and Liton is standing his ground. Hashmatullah Shahidi is the fielder. It's 50/50. He lunged forward and the ball lodged in his right hand with his left hand coming off. His head was up high, didn't look at the ball going in to protect his face so he may genuinely not have known if it carried or not. And the third umpire has decided it is OUT! Third umpire is Aleem Dar. The soft signal on field was out and he said he didn't see anything conclusive to overturn on the mic'd up conversation. Those kinds of catches are regularly overturned. It'll generate plenty of debate for sure. It looked awkward at any rate as both hands were not under the ball, just the right one.

commentary: Mohammad Nabi to Tamim Iqbal, OUT castled! Nabi with the rope a dope the ball before floating up a sucker ball to get Tamim on the back foot, this time zips one in slightly quicker and flatter on a good to fullish length at 82 kph/51 mph, Tamim into the habit of consistently going onto the back foot when he should've come forward for this, this one skids on from fourth stump line to crash into off stump, beating the back foot slap. Bangladesh momentum arrested temporarily.
shortText: Mohammad Nabi to Tamim Iqbal, OUT
text: castled! Nabi with the rope a dope the ball before floating up a sucker ball to get Tamim on the back foot, this time zips one in slightly quicker and flatter on a good to fullish length at 82 kph/51 mph, Tamim into the habit of consistently going onto the back foot when he should've come forward for this, this one skids on from fourth stump line to crash into off stump, beating the back foot slap. Bangladesh momentum arrested temporarily.

commentary: Rashid Khan to Shakib Al Hasan, no run double-strike for Afghanistan! Rashid gets a good length ball pitching on middle stump to straighten and skid on but Shakib calls for the review! Looked stone dead live. Hit on the knee roll with Shakib striding a touch forward. And ball-tracking shows it's going over the stumps on height! Great review by Shakib. Is there any doubt that this is his tournament?

commentary: Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Shakib Al Hasan, OUT he's got him! Shakib not reviewing. Length ball skids past the inside edge as he gets forward and raps him in front of middle stump. Was that angling down? Could have been, but Shakib doesn't think so. And he's right, replays confirm. Walks straight off. Mujeeb has done it. He has quietly had a very good World Cup. commentary: Mujeeb Ur Rahman to Soumya Sarkar, OUT lbw decision review by Sarkar. He's caught right in front of middle to a full ball, trying to flick it. It's a legbreak this time. Has it done enough to miss leg? The stump is half visible on the early replay...and tracking says it is clipping it. Umpire's call. Bangladesh retain their review, but they've lost Sarkar - who already looked quite lost at No. 5. Liton was probably pushed up today to counter Mujeeb, and we've seen why

commentary: Rashid Khan to Mahmudullah, 1 run good length ball clipped to midwicket off the back foot. Mushfiqur turned and wanted two but doesn't see that Mahmudullah is limping to the non-striker's end for the first run. commentary: Dawlat Zadran to Mahmudullah, 1 run good length ball prodded to cover, Mahmudullah hobbles out of his crease looking for a run. Mushfiqur wasn't going to risk selling himself out for a partner on one leg. Shinwari fields in the ring and spins to fire wildly past the stumps with Mahmudullah well in. The line of the throw makes it impossible for a back-up fielder to be in position and they steal an overthrow.

commentary: Rashid Khan to Mosaddek Hossain, 2 runs full on off, tries to flick through midwicket again with no fielders in the on side ring, leading edge balloons toward extra cover, Gulbadin slow to react running forward, lunges as the ball lands short and goes under him for a pair. Microcosm of Afghanistan's fielding all day. Consistently a step too slow.

commentary: Dawlat Zadran to Mosaddek Hossain, 1 run another misfired yorker, but this one at ankle height on middle stump this time around so no width to drive, and a single is pushed to long-off.

commentary: Dawlat Zadran to Mushfiqur Rahim, OUT Mushfiqur's superb effort ends with a skier to Nabi at extra cover! It was in the slot full outside off, just got under it way too much trying to clear the off side ring. Goes high to Nabi backpedaling from the circle and he takes it safely. Mushfiqur has set up Bangladesh beautifully on a track offering plenty of turn. Every run valuable on what is expected to be a tough chasing track used for a second match.

commentary: Gulbadin Naib to Mohammad Saifuddin, 1 run dropped! Frankly embarrassing from Dawlat. The same man who dropped Eoin Morgan on 26 on the boundary off Rashid in the England match produces the worst effort of the day - and there are plenty to choose from across these 50 overs. Gorgeous slower ball from Gulbadin landing wide outside off is sliced softly in the air to backward point. Dawlat runs to his right in front of Asghar moving left from short third man. He spills a dolly at head height. 2/10 on degree of difficulty.

commentary: Mosaddek Hossain to Hashmatullah Shahidi, no run should've been a runout! Hashmatullah chopped a short ball well wide of cover for what should have been an easy run after the ball was only partially knocked down by Liton Das at extra cover and squirted well away for a run. Both he and Gulbadin stopped midpitch to admire the scenery on the boundary. Mehidy backs up the misfield from point with Gulbadin still halfway down the pitch after Hashmatullah ran back. But he rushed the throw to Mosaddek over the stumps and dragged him two yards away to reprieve Gulbadin. An accurate relay would have had him out by 3 yards. Mosaddek is furious at Mehidy.

commentary: Mosaddek Hossain to Hashmatullah Shahidi, OUT lovely flight and lovely stumping! Hashmatullah had itchy feet from the start of the over with a series of premeditated shuffles down the pitch. He got the itch again tempted out with a well flighted ball that was dragged slightly back and slightly wider on a fifth stump line. Hashmatullah doesn't cover the line and is beaten by the turn. Sharp work by Mushfiqur to whip the bails off with Hashmatullah's back foot flailing about three inches short of getting back in.

commentary: Shakib Al Hasan to Gulbadin Naib, OUT brilliant field placing captaincy by Mashrafe! They had a man at short mid-off a little while ago and Liton was moved a touch wider at short extra cover at about 17 yards. The ball has been stopping a touch on this pitch all day with flicks and drives going slightly uppish in the ring and on this occasion Gulbadin laces a flat drive to Liton, who claims a catch at ankle height crouching slightly forward. Shakib erupts, as does the partisan Bangladesh crowd! 8/10 on degree of difficulty due to the pace it came at Liton from short range but it was straight to him on line.

commentary: Shakib Al Hasan to Mohammad Nabi, OUT Bangladesh's king of the tourney castles the President of Afghanistan! It was a beauty flighted on fourth stump and skidded on with Nabi's technique exposed. He gave a half-hearted stride forward prodding with a gap between bat and pad. The ball clips the inside edge before ricocheting onto leg stump. Shakib is rocking this tournament!

commentary: Shakib Al Hasan to Asghar Afghan, OUT Shakib you monster! Asghar was bogged down and looked desperate to get off strike previous ball. He shuffles back and forth side to side across the crease as Shakib approached this time and finally stopped moving with his feet outside leg stump as Shakib floated one full on middle. Asghar goes for the slog sweep as a release shot in frustration, too much elevation and not enough distance. Basic catch taken at waist height 8 yards in from the rope.
